<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-09-08T23:35:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-09-08T23:35:00-05:00" n="449" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d449">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">391.1115/12: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Dreyfus</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-09-09T08:00:00+03:25">September 9, 1941—8
                                        a.m.</date><lb/>[Received September 10—9:35 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>142. Although communications have still not been reestablished
                                throughout the country I have had indirect word from all places
                                where we have citizens and believe it safe now to state that all
                                Americans in Iran are safe.</p>
                            <p>Please inform Presbyterian Mission Board.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Dreyfus</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>